B
P(A^{c} \cap B) = P(B)-P(B \cap A)  
= P(B)-P(B)P(A)
= P(B)[1-P(A)]
= P(B)P(A^{c})
P(A^{c} \cap B) = P(A^{c})-P(A^{c} \cap B^{c})
A^{c}
B^{c}
P(A^c \cap B)=P(A^c)-P(A^c\cap B^c)
A^c \cap B^c=(A \cup B)^c
\begin{align*}P((A \cup B)^c)&=1-P(A \cup B)\\&=1-P(A)-P(B)+P(A \cap B)\\&\overset{ind}{=}1-P(A)-P(B)+P(A) \cdot P(B)\\&=(1-P(A))\cdot(1-P(B))\\&=P(A^c)\cdot P(B^c)\end{align*}
